docs.lead_paragraph: Doctors have reported two more cases of suicidal behavior and suicidal fantasies that they believe can only be explained by the effects of the widely publicized antidepressant drug Prozac. The new cases were described in a letter in today's issue of The New England Journal of Medicine. The physicians said the two cases differed from previous published reports of suicidal behavior linked to Prozac because the two patients had never before shown signs of wanting to kill themselves.

headline.main: Suicidal Behavior Tied Again to Drug
